ning with Reagan has put children of immigrants and refugees in detention camps. Yet these tactics of terror have encountered opposition from every generation, and Briggs challenges us to stand and resist in this powerful corrective to American history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aChild welfarezCentral AmericaxDecision making. 0aChild welfarezUnited StatesxDecision making. 0aJuvenile detentionzCentral America. 0aJuvenile detentionzUnited States. 7aHISTORY / United States / General.2bisacsh  aadoption.  aamerican history.  aassimilation.  aasylum.  ababies.  ablack children.  ablack freedom movement.  aboarding schools.  acentral america.  achildren.  acommunism.  acoup.  acrack babies.  adetention camps.  aethnic studies.  afoster care.  ahistory.  ahuman rights.  aimmigrants.  aindigenous children.  aindigenous peoples.  alatinx.  amission schools.  anative american missionary schools.  anative children.  anonfiction.  apolitics.  apoverty.  apublic policy.  areeducation.  arefugees.  areproductive rights.  aslavery.  asocial issues.  asocial justice.  awelfare.  awesternization.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069041540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520975071zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520975071423Coveruhttps://